ACCT 5375 - Advanced International Financial Reporting
Introduces and interprets accounting issues unique to multinational
enterprises and international business activity. Course include
International Financial Reporting Standards (IFRS); financial reporting
outside the USA; formulation of international financial data; comparison
of IFRS and US GAAP; evaluate international financial disclosure issues
such as environmental; accounting harmonization; ethics; taxation;
foreign exchange; and cultural issues.
Prerequisite: ACCT 3312 and admission to the Master of Accountancy
program or consent of the MAcc program director.
